Musk seeks delivery record
Tesla's quarter may be record-breaking. Despite the boom in deliveries, the electric car company has seen losses recently.
New York. Tesla boss Elon Musk has given his electric car company a strong boost on the stock market with the prospect of new record numbers. "We have the opportunity to reach 100,000 deliveries in our first quarter," Musk wrote in an email to Tesla employees published by industry blog Electrek.
